properties.Name: CustomerUccFiling
properties.Description:
UCC filing are reports filed at the state level that indicate assets that are pledged as collateral by the Customer.

Collateral goods must abide by state law.

The security interest is legalized by filing a document with the state called a UCC Form 1/UCC Form 2, Financing Statement.   This details that the seller will have priority to the collateral over competing claims by other creditors or government.

Columns.Name: UccFilingNumber
Columns.Description: The unique identifier of the UCC filing.

Columns.Name: DateFiled
Columns.Description: The date that the filing was made.

Columns.Name: FinancingStatement
Columns.Description: The formal financing statement associated with the UCC Filing.

Columns.Name: CustomerId
Columns.Description: The unique identifier of a Customer.
